This does fix the first two things I mentioned earlier. But globalstatus or laststatus=3 is still broken.

@justinmk laststatus=3 or globalstatus was introduced to consolidate multiple statuslines into just one at the end of neovim-screen. It's a bit different then other laststatus options. In that sense with globalstatus set floating windows should utilize that global-statusline too instead of having one for each floating window. With that, we basically go back to the time before globalstatus.

for context: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/17266
